---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHero from '@components/ui/SectionHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research"
  description="ZAI Institute conducts structured qualitative research with senior operators on enterprise AI adoption. Custom engagements, subscription intelligence, and published reports."
>
  <SectionHero
    eyebrow="Research"
    title="Structured intelligence from the people doing the work."
    lede="The institute's research function does one thing well: structured interviews with senior operators across the Fortune 500 and the AI platform companies that serve them. What we learn informs our published reports, the custom studies partners commission, and the standing intelligence we deliver to subscribers. The work is operator-grade, built for the people making the decision, not for the people writing the briefing deck."
  />

  <section class="bg-paper text-ink">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 md:py-24 space-y-16">

      <div>
        <h2 class="eyebrow eyebrow-on-light mb-4">Methodology</h2>
        <div class="max-w-prose-wide space-y-4 text-body text-ink/90">
          <p>
            Every study begins with a structured interview protocol designed around the question
            being asked. We recruit senior operators, typically VPs, SVPs, and the C-suite, at the
            companies that actually face the decision. Interviews are conducted by trained
            researchers, not salespeople.
          </p>
          <p>
            Participation is consented and disclosed up front. Everyone we speak with knows their
            input contributes to published research, and that what we publish is aggregated and
            de-identified. We do not attribute a finding to a person or a company by name.
          </p>
          <p>
            Quantitative validation comes through structured surveys across our wider executive
            network. Synthesis turns the research into findings, never into a list of who said what.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule-muted" />

      <div>
        <h2 class="eyebrow eyebrow-on-light mb-4">What we publish</h2>
        <div class="max-w-prose-wide space-y-4 text-body text-ink/90">
          <p>
            Our published research, the AI Readiness Gap and the AI Skills Gap, draws on responses
            from across the network. The pattern that holds across both: the strategy gap is wider
            than the skills gap.
          </p>
          <p>
            Organizations can deploy AI. Most still cannot measure whether it is improving the
            business. That single finding is the question the institute's work keeps returning to.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule-muted" />

      <div>
        <h2 class="eyebrow eyebrow-on-light mb-4">Custom engagements</h2>
        <div class="max-w-prose-wide space-y-4 text-body text-ink/90">
          <p>
            Some of the institute's research is commissioned by enterprises, AI platform companies,
            and investment firms with a specific question the public reports do not answer.
            Engagements come in three tiers, distinguished by scope, sample size, and depth of
            synthesis.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="font-sans font-semibold">The smallest tier</strong> answers a defined,
            sector- or function-specific question.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="font-sans font-semibold">The middle tier</strong> supports broader
            portfolio decisions and adds structured surveys on top of the interviews.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="font-sans font-semibold">The largest tier</strong> is built for
            organizations weighing a major directional decision over several quarters, with multiple
            interview cohorts and embedded analyst time.
          </p>
          <p>
            Every engagement delivers synthesized findings. It does not deliver raw interviews or
            the identities of participants. All three begin with a discovery conversation that
            defines the question and scopes the work. Pricing is shared in that conversation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule-muted" />

      <div>
        <h2 class="eyebrow eyebrow-on-light mb-4">Subscription intelligence</h2>
        <div class="max-w-prose-wide space-y-4 text-body text-ink/90">
          <p>
            Subscription intelligence is a standing relationship for organizations that need
            continuous signal rather than one-time research. Subscribers receive regular briefings
            on the patterns emerging across the institute's work, early access to published
            findings, and quarterly sessions with the institute's principal researchers.
          </p>
          <p>
            What subscribers receive is the institute's synthesis: the aggregated, de-identified
            intelligence drawn from the full body of research. It is built for AI platform
            companies, large enterprises with active AI portfolios, and investment firms with
            AI-heavy theses. Annual commitment. Single seat or organization-wide.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule-muted" />

      <div>
        <h2 class="eyebrow eyebrow-on-light mb-4">The Executive Benchmark Report</h2>
        <div class="max-w-prose-wide space-y-4 text-body text-ink/90">
          <p>
            The institute's flagship is forthcoming: a recurring benchmark on how organizations are
            actually measuring the business impact of AI, drawn from the full breadth of our
            research. It is the clearest expression of what the institute exists to do, turn the
            real experience of senior operators into an honest read on what is working and what is
            not.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule-muted" />

      <div>
        <h2 class="eyebrow eyebrow-on-light mb-4">Published research</h2>
        <div class="max-w-prose-wide space-y-4 text-body text-ink/90">
          <p>
            The institute publishes the work it considers most useful to the field, free to read,
            no registration. Current reports cover AI readiness in the Fortune 500, the AI skills
            gap in the workforce, and the agent readiness gap in the enterprise. New reports
            release as the work supports them.
          </p>
          <p>The published library is the strongest single signal of what the institute actually does.</p>
          <p>
            <a href="/insights" class="text-sm font-medium text-gold-deep border-b border-gold pb-0.5 hover:text-ink">
              Browse published research &rsaquo;
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-ink text-paper">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 md:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-prose-wide">
        <div class="eyebrow mb-6">Commission research</div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-h2 text-paper">Start with a discovery conversation.</h2>
        <p class="mt-6 text-body-lg text-paper/85 max-w-prose-narrow">
          Tell us what you are trying to decide and what you have already considered. We will tell
          you whether commissioned research is the right answer, which tier fits, and what the next
          thirty days would look like. The first conversation is one hour. Pricing is shared in that
          conversation if there is a fit.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-10">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Commission research</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
